                    "description": "As a financial investigator at the Dutch Safety Board, I am responsible for the investigation of financial aspects of an accident or disaster. By investigating the (decision-making process of) financial aspects of the accident, the Dutch Safety Board can draw conclusions to enable the industry to learn from the accident from a financial perspective.\n\nType of financial aspects I investigate:\n- Financial system of an industry;\n- Ownership, shareholding;\n- Decision-making processes and it's financial incentives;\n- Process of public procurement and tenders;\n- (Lack of) investments;\n- Financial position of parties involved;\n- Prices, tariffs,\n- and everything else with a financial aspect.\n\nSince this is a new position within the Dutch Safety Board, I am also working on the implementation of 'research from a financial point of view', embedding investigating financial aspects in the organisation.",
